# Environment variables for AI Humanizer (local development)

# --- Firebase Auth (required for social login) ---
# Obtain these from Firebase Console: Project Settings → Your apps → Config
REACT_APP_FIREBASE_API_KEY=your_api_key_here
REACT_APP_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=your-project-id.firebaseapp.com
REACT_APP_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=your_project_id_here

# --- Optional Firebase fields (only if your setup uses them) ---
# If present in your Firebase web config, you may also include:
# REACT_APP_FIREBASE_APP_ID=your_app_id_here
# REACT_APP_FIREBASE_MEASUREMENT_ID=G-XXXXXXXXXX

# --- Service Worker cache-busting (optional) ---
# Set a fixed version string to control SW update detection across deployments.
# If omitted, a timestamp will be used at runtime.
# REACT_APP_SW_VERSION=1

# Instructions:
# 1) Copy this file to ".env.local" in the project root.
# 2) Fill in valid values from your Firebase web app config.
# 3) Ensure Google and/or GitHub providers are enabled in Firebase Authentication.
# 4) Add "localhost" to Authorized Domains in Firebase Authentication settings.
# 5) Restart the dev server after changes.